<item>
            <title>[LU-669] mea.c unconditionally uses ldiskfs hashs</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-669</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Remove the ldiskfs hash code from mea.c as described by comment 15 in Lustre bugzilla 22410.  The MEA_MAGIC_HASH_SEGMENT case has been replaced with a CERROR() which will indicate if this ever occurs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Yes, the two level hashing function is implemented in this patch.  And there no ldiskfs hash dependency on client anymore, so those ldiskfs hash function can be removed from mea.c&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;#8211; wangdi&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was originally filed as Lustre bugzilla 22410.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
